sentences.english: Other agreements in 1880 and 1892 sealed the protectorate status of Bahrain to the British.
sentences.chinese: 1892年的協定確定了巴林是英國的保護國。

sentences.english: Each also served as protective patron for many non-nuclear nations.
sentences.chinese: 它們還各自充當許多無核武器國家的保護國。

sentences.english: Great Britain's interest in the Suez Canal led to the establishment of a British protectorate .
sentences.chinese: 英國在蘇伊士運河的興趣導致了英國保護國的成立。

sentences.english: It was also presented to all those who later participated in the creation of the protectorates of Bohemia and Moravia.
sentences.chinese: 還授予後來在波希米亞和摩拉維亞建立保護國的人員。

sentences.english: Zanzibar became independent, after being a British Protectorate since 1890.
sentences.chinese: 自1890年以來一直是英國保護國的桑給巴爾獨立。
